<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/57103003-lb"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/57103003-lb">LB</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I taught ESL for many years. We never assigned this book to any ESL students, including advanced. The language is pretty difficult. However, there is <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I taught ESL for many years. We never assigned this book to any ESL students, including advanced. The language is pretty difficult. However, there is no harm in trying. In the worst case scenario, you'll just put it down. Good luck!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
