<span id="freeTextContainer8843235253508103328">This book raises dullness of style to sublimely convoluted heights. It&apos;s really one of the oddest books, stylistically, I&apos;ve ever read. I read it years ago and I still can&apos;t pinpoint the source of this oddness, though I suspect it&apos;s the sheer complex awkwardness of the prose, which reminded me of something Henry James might&apos;ve written if forced to type into a BlackBerry with his elbows.</span>
  <span id="freeText8843235253508103328" style="display:none">This book raises dullness of style to sublimely convoluted heights. It's really one of the oddest books, stylistically, I've ever read. I read it years ago and I still can't pinpoint the source of this oddness, though I suspect it's the sheer complex awkwardness of the prose, which reminded me of something Henry James might've written if forced to type into a BlackBerry with his elbows.</span>
